---

<section class="parallax-section editorial-section" id="aimo-references">
  <div class="editorial-container">
    <div class="editorial-content">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="editorial-symbol">üß©</span>
          <h2 class="editorial-heading">Artistic References</h2>
          <p class="editorial-caption parallax-text">Visual and conceptual inspirations</p>
        </div>

        <div class="references-content">
          <p class="editorial-text intro-text">
            AIMo's visual and conceptual world draws inspiration from:
          </p>

          <div class="references-grid">
            <div class="reference-card">
              <h3 class="reference-title">Kandinsky</h3>
              <p class="reference-description">
                for his pursuit of harmony between form and sound, and the belief that each line and color has an inner soul.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="reference-card">
              <h3 class="reference-title">Paul Klee</h3>
              <p class="reference-description">
                for his lightness and the idea of drawings that "come alive."
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="reference-card">
              <h3 class="reference-title">Constructivist Art</h3>
              <p class="reference-description">
                and digital wireframe art, where structure itself becomes language.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="wireframe-concept">
            <p class="concept-text">
              The wireframe penguin symbolizes a <strong>form in progress</strong> ‚Äî a mind constantly sketching itself, 
              a diagram of thought.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

